You really don't know, do you?
Know what?

39:04.000 --> 39:05.558
Well, your partner here

39:05.610 --> 39:07.464
decided to give me
a shot in the arm.

39:07.510 --> 39:09.034
He'd get me back
on the horse.

39:09.080 --> 39:12.140
He spoon-fed me the clues
so I could find Menck.

39:12.180 --> 39:14.910
Gareth, those files
were my idea. He didn't even...

39:14.950 --> 39:17.077
You don't know him
like I know him.

39:17.120 --> 39:19.680
In fact, you don't know
how well he knows you.

39:21.460 --> 39:23.781
You and your
voices, Sherlock.

39:23.820 --> 39:25.981
I don't know who I
preferred more, actually,

39:26.030 --> 39:27.429
Pelfrey or Phillips.

39:27.460 --> 39:29.758
Though I have to say
that asking me out

39:29.800 --> 39:31.825
for a cup of coffee
was a really nice touch.

39:31.870 --> 39:33.792
I was actually quite
flattered, to be honest.

39:33.830 --> 39:35.798
You should have seen
me there, though,

39:35.840 --> 39:37.592
sitting there,
Shawn Menck's apartment.

39:37.640 --> 39:40.131
I just couldn't believe
how easy it was

39:40.170 --> 39:42.070
to find all of
that evidence.

39:42.110 --> 39:44.135
Three of the wallets
sitting neatly stacked

39:44.180 --> 39:45.841
on a little table.

39:45.880 --> 39:47.643
I thought it was
impossible.

39:47.680 --> 39:51.480
But then... just as
I was about to leave,

39:51.520 --> 39:54.614
I found this.

39:54.660 --> 39:56.389
Yes.

39:57.860 --> 39:59.122
It's a rooster feather.

39:59.160 --> 40:02.197
Just like the ones
on your pets.

40:02.230 --> 40:04.460
You'd set the table for me,
hadn't you, Sherlock?

40:04.500 --> 40:06.627
But you just done too good
a job of it.

40:06.670 --> 40:08.126
You see, if I hadn't found this,

40:08.170 --> 40:10.138
_ I'd still be out
mopIng around thIs brownstone

40:10.170 --> 40:13.207
with a right old
bog on. But no,

40:13.240 --> 40:14.832
thanks to seeing
through a plot devised

40:14.880 --> 40:17.178
by the great Sherlock Holmes,
I have decided

40:17.210 --> 40:19.644
to give detecting
one last chance.

40:19.680 --> 40:21.568
So I accepted a
job this morning.

40:21.620 --> 40:25.738
Yeah, it's a consultant
position with the Garda in Cork.

40:25.790 --> 40:29.055
Wait-- the Garda, as in
the Irish National Police?

40:29.090 --> 40:30.648
Yes, that's right.
I leave tomorrow.

40:30.690 --> 40:32.749
So I've got rather a
lot of packing to do.

40:32.790 --> 40:34.155
So if you'll excuse me.

40:34.190 --> 40:35.851
Unless, of course,
you want to continue

40:35.900 --> 40:37.151
this ridiculous charade,
Sherlock,

40:37.200 --> 40:39.964
I will quite happily stay.

40:52.710 --> 40:55.543
Well played, sir.

40:55.580 --> 40:57.969
Well played.

41:02.890 --> 41:04.778
Well...

41:08.060 --> 41:10.620
Now... I wouldn't

41:10.660 --> 41:12.867
feel too bad about
him leaving you

41:12.900 --> 41:14.663
in the dark, Joan.

41:14.700 --> 41:16.258
I mean, you have to
understand, of course,

41:16.300 --> 41:19.758
you are in the infancy
of your partnership.

41:19.810 --> 41:22.608
Having spent as much
time as I did with him,

41:22.640 --> 41:24.972
you'll figure
him out as well.

41:32.220 --> 41:33.778
(beeping)

41:35.320 --> 41:37.151
to help him
these last couple of days,

41:37.190 --> 41:39.784
because you had your own plan
to build him up?

41:39.830 --> 41:41.695
I've never heard
of Shawn Menck,

41:41.730 --> 41:43.994
Roscoe Pelfrey or
Carlton Phillips.

41:44.030 --> 41:46.965
I did not manipulate
those files.

41:47.000 --> 41:48.661
However easy it may have been,

41:48.700 --> 41:50.895
Lestrade closed that case
on hIs own.

41:50.940 --> 41:52.703
The conspiracy he's describing

41:52.740 --> 41:55.903
is a product of his obviously
very fertile imagination.

41:55.940 --> 41:58.135
As far as the feather
that he found,

41:58.180 --> 42:00.000
that's a classic case
of transference.

42:00.050 --> 42:02.746
It fell from his clothes,
not mine.

42:02.780 --> 42:04.179
But you just said...

42:04.220 --> 42:06.643
What I thought would be
most helpful to him.

42:06.690 --> 42:08.248
You were right.

42:08.290 --> 42:10.952
And the more he talked,
the clearer it became.

42:10.990 --> 42:12.321
In some cases,

42:12.360 --> 42:15.523
there are other ways
to assist a friend.

42:17.800 --> 42:20.667
So what does that one do
once it ticks down?

42:20.700 --> 42:24.261
Spray you with water,
make a loud noise?

42:24.300 --> 42:25.904
It explodes.

42:25.940 --> 42:27.134
I told my colleague
I wanted more

42:27.170 --> 42:28.535
of a challenge,
and he sent me this.

42:29.840 --> 42:31.102
Oh.

42:33.150 --> 42:35.243
You're staying?

42:35.280 --> 42:38.716
Mmm, what can I say?
I have faith.

